{
  "stem": "2522.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Continually arguing, well, it can't be that bad.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Well, maybe I'll do this, maybe I'll compromise on that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Maybe it won't be that way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And besides, I don't know what's on the other side-- this continual [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] dialogue back and forth.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I, I, I mention it to you, Eli, as an incremental rationalization, which, to me, is one of the very dominant themes of-- that lead me to explain lots of things that I've observed in the Holocaust, that, that people, for a number of reasons, were continually forced to incrementally rationalize whatever position they took, although that incremental rationalization was a one-way street towards destruction.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh there was discussion.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and, of course, it was Israel, although Israel was very unsettled.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, of course, there was problems with aliyah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We had people who came who offered us to go to Madagascar.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then there was this Romanian who came and who was selling Cuban visas.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, there was all sorts of very interesting things.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But they were always rationalized and argued about, never very conclusively.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was-- I was in Hashomer Hatzair at camp in the High Tatras in September 1, 1939, when the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we actually could hear the German guns destroying the Polish army.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
